                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1074">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.801/6–2749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-27">June 27,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received June 27—11:25 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2504. A check with local steamship companies indicates that all ships scheduled
                    Shanghai near future cancelled. Reuters reported that Far Eastern freight
                    conference meeting Oslo last week recommended to all members that ships not call
                    North China ports. Shanghai Pilots Association has had no contact with pilot
                    vessel at mouth Yangtze since June 22. British bombed vessel <hi rend="italic"
                        >Anchises</hi> floated and moved up Whangpoo to Holts Wharf for discharge
                    cargo. No other foreign vessel in port.</p>
                <p>Repeated Nanking 1362, Canton 809.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
